sequenceDiagram
title OIDC Auth Flow: Next.js + Next-Auth + AWS Cognito
autonumber

participant User
participant Nextjs as Next.js Server (Next-Auth)
participant Cognito as AWS Cognito (IdP)
participant DB as Database / Mirama API

%% Initiation
User ->> Nextjs: Click "Login"
Nextjs ->> Cognito: Redirect to /oauth2/authorize (PKCE)
activate Cognito

%% Authentication (Social or Local)
alt Google Social Login
    Cognito ->> User: Redirect to Google
    User ->> Cognito: Google Auth Success
else Username/Password
    Cognito ->> User: Show Hosted UI / Login Form
    User ->> Cognito: Submit Credentials
end

%% Callback & Code Exchange
Cognito ->> Nextjs: Redirect to /api/auth/callback/cognito?code=XYZ
deactivate Cognito
activate Nextjs

Nextjs ->> Cognito: Exchange Code for Tokens (ID, Access, Refresh)
activate Cognito
Cognito -->> Nextjs: Return JWT Tokens
deactivate Cognito

%% Database Sync and User Validation
Note over Nextjs, DB: Next-Auth Callback
Nextjs ->> DB: Fetch/Update User (by Email/Sub)
activate DB
DB -->> Nextjs: Return App-Specific Metadata (TenantId, OrgID, UserID, RoleId)
deactivate DB

%% 5. Session Establishment
Note over Nextjs: Next.js signs its own Session JWT
Nextjs -->> User: Set Secure HTTP-only Cookie
deactivate Nextjs

%% 6. Authenticated Request
User ->> Nextjs: Request Protected Resource
activate Nextjs
Nextjs ->> DB: Query Data using Next.js Access Token Context
DB -->> Nextjs: Return Data
Nextjs -->> User: Render Page with Data
deactivate Nextjs